-- File: supabase/migrations/00162_meramec_niangua_geometry_extend.sql
-- Extend two curated mainstems whose lines stopped short of their own
-- rating gauges, leaving those gauges rendering as "phantom" markers in a
-- blank basin on /river-map:
--
--   * meramec: the line began ~10 river-miles DOWNSTREAM of USGS 07010350
--     (Meramec River at Cook Station) — the whole upper Meramec was missing.
--     Extended upstream from the old start through Cook Station to the
--     headwaters near Salem.
--   * niangua: the line ended ~4 miles UPSTREAM of USGS 06923950 (Niangua
--     River at Tunnel Dam) — extended downstream through the Tunnel Dam
--     gauge.
--
-- Source: USGS NLDI mainstem navigation (UM/DM flowlines from the NWIS
-- sites, NHDPlus HR geometry), stitched onto the existing lines (join gaps
-- < 80 m), Douglas-Peucker simplified at ~25 m. Verified post-extend:
-- 07010350 sits 0.02 mi from the meramec line, 06923950 sits 0.02 mi from
-- the niangua line; every other mainstem gauge is unchanged at 0.00 mi.
-- (07018500 Big River at Byrnesville and 07017200 Big River at Irondale
-- remain intentionally off-line — they are proxy raters on a stream the map
-- does not draw, and the map hides off-line gauge markers.)

